    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a6037e5_8ae8ab78",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/host/libs/libOpenglRender/FrameBuffer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 770,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-18T23:28:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "should we only add/remove it if refcount is 1 for open and 0 for close?\n\nUpdate: I see that you\u0027re using a multiset here to take care of reference counting.\nit\u0027s less efficient, but works too. Also you would call close() multiple times if a color buffer has been opened more than once.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 770,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 770,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "a93a9e1a9155247a1639a32023c8b8e88edc6781",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a6037e5_cd4d9d6f",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/host/libs/libOpenglRender/FrameBuffer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 770,
      "author": {
        "id": 1087303
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-19T00:00:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Your suggestion makes sense. The only problem is that it is unclear to me what is the expected behavior if a process opens a color buffer multiple times. Does it only need to close the color buffer one time or it needs to close it multiple times? The current implementation assumes it needs to be close one time for each open, so that it behaves more similar to the original implementation.\n\nThe behavior doesn\u0027t seem to be specified here:\nhttps://cs.corp.google.com/aosp-master/hardware/libhardware/include/hardware/gralloc.h\n\nIf you know about the expected behavior, please tell me. (I need to convince myself to dump multi-set)",
      "parentUuid": "6a6037e5_8ae8ab78",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 770,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 770,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "a93a9e1a9155247a1639a32023c8b8e88edc6781",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
